storeOverflowDataInBuffer(byte[], int, int, int) - Method in class core.eeg.storage.MbtDataBuffering
Stores a part of the EEG raw data inside the oveflowBytes buffer in case packet size is too large for buffer As the overflowing data part is the part of the data source array that has not been stored in the pending data buffer, the beginning position is [srcPos + rawDataBufferSize - bufPos] and the number of components stored is equal to rawDataPacketSize - length.
